INSERT INTO `proj_Item` VALUES (1,'Aegis of the Immortal','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/aegis-of-the-immortal.png','Aegis of the Immortal\nPassive: Reincarnation\n\nBrings you to life with full health and mana 5 seconds after you die, at the location where you died. Reincarnation must be used within 5 minutes or Aegis of the Immortal disappears. If it expires, it will heal you over 5 seconds (dispels on damage).\n\nEffect Delay: 5\nExpire Max Health Restored per Second: 20%\nExpire Max Mana Restored per Second: 20%\nExpire Restore Duration: 5\n\nThe Immortal was said to own a shield that protected him from death itself.\nAdditional Information\nNotes:\n\nIf the wielder is  Wraith King,  Reincarnation triggers first if it\'s off cooldown.\nRevives with full health and mana. Spells and items are not refreshed.\nProvides temporary ground vision near your death area while reincarnating.\nWhen expiring, restores in form of health and mana regeneration, so it restores 0.2% of maximum health and mana in 0.01 second intervals.\nThe hero\'s max health and mana are checked periodically and the values adapted instantly.\nSince it heals for a fixed percentage over a fixed duration, it doesn\'t always guarantee a full heal.\nSo if the hero\'s health or mana drop by a significant amount (health drop through HP removal) during the heal, it may not be at full health or mana once the heal expires.\nIs dispelled by any damage greater than 20 (before reductions), including self afflicted damage.\nIs not dispelled by health cost of spells, health manipulating spells, negative regeneration,  Poison Sting and  Dispersion.\nIs always dispelled by attacks, even when the attack dealt no damage.\nFully stacks with other health and mana regeneration increasing effects.'),(2,'Aeon Disk','Shops: Main Shop\nPassive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 1100  Total Cost: 3100','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/aeon-disk.png','Aeon Disk\nBonus:\n+300 Health\n+300 Mana\n\nPassive: Combo Breaker\n\nWhenever you take damage and are below 70% health, you apply a strong dispel on your hero and you gain a 2.5 second buff that grants 75% status resistance and reduces all incoming and outgoing damage to zero. Only triggers on player-based damage.\n\n\n\n\n 105\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPassive: Status Resistance\n\nReduces status effect durations by 25%.'),(3,'Aether Lens','Recipe Cost: 600  Total Cost: 2350','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/aether-lens.png','Aether Lens\n+450 Mana\n+3 Mana Regeneration\n+250 Cast Range\n\nAethereal Focus\n\nIncreases targeted spell and item cast range by 250.\nAdditional Information\nPolished with the incantation of his final breath, the gift of a dying mage to his sickly son.'),(4,'Aghanim\'s Scepter','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Caster\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 4200','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/aghanims-scepter.png','Aghanim\'s Scepter\nBonus:\n+10 Strength\n+10 Agility\n+10 Intelligence\n+200 HP\n+150 Mana\n\nPassive: Ultimate Upgrade\n\nUpgrades the ultimate and some abilities of certain heroes.\nAdditional Information\nThe scepter of a wizard with demigod-like powers.\n\nNotes:\n\nWhen a hero has an upgrade available, the item\'s and the upgraded spell\'s tool tip state what exactly is upgraded.\nWhen a hero has no upgrades available, the ultimate ability gets a green note reading \"This hero has no upgrade\".\n\n\n\n\nUpgraded Ultimates\n\n\n\nTips:\n(Using the Ctrl+F (Find) function will help you immensely in finding what you\'re looking)\n\n Abaddon - Increases duration from 4/5/6 to (5/6/7*) and redirects 35% of all damage dealt to nearby allied heroes in a 900 unit radius to  Abaddon when active.\n\n Alchemist - Alchemist can cast  Aghanim\'s Scepter on an ally or himself, granting the hero all Aghanim\'s stats and their upgrades.  Aghanim\'s Scepter is consumed in the process.\n\n Ancient Apparition - Increases duration from 8/9/10 to (17*)\n\n Axe - Decreases cooldown from 75/65/55 to (6*) (0**), increases kill threshold from 250/350/450 to (300/450/625*), and increases the duration of movement speed upon kill from 6 to (10*).\n\n Bane - Increases damage per second from 100/155/215 to (155 / 215 / 270*), mana drain from 5% to (10%*) of target\'s max mana, and duration from 5 to (7*). If an enemy tries to attack  Bane while he is channeling  Fiend\'s Grip, they will instantly have  Bane\'s current level of  Nightmare inflicted upon them.\n\n Beastmaster - Decreases cooldown from 80/75/70 to (45*), increases cast range from 600 to (950*).\n\n Brewmaster - Gives  Thunder Clap to Earth, Drunken Haze to Storm, and  Drunken Brawler to Fire, at the same level as the original  Brewmaster and with independent cooldowns from the original  Brewmaster.\n\n Centaur Warrunner  - Reduces all incoming damage by 70% and grants allies unobstructed movement.\n\n Chen - Reduces cooldown from 160/140/120 to (30*). Allows  Holy Persuasion to target 0 (1/2/3*) Ancient Creeps.\n\n Clockwerk - Decreases cooldown from 70/55/40 (12*).\n\n Crystal Maiden - Increases damage from 105/170/250 to (170/250/310*) and slow from 30% to (50%*).\n\n Dark Seer - Increases the damage dealt by illusions from 70%/80%/90% to (100%/120%/140%*).\n\n Dazzle - Increases radius from 575 to (775*) and armor per second from 0.75/1.0/1.25 to (1.25/1.5/1.75*).\n\n Disruptor -  Static Storm silences items, and lasts an extra 2 seconds (from 5 to (7*)). Increases maximum damage per second from 200/250/300 to (280/350/420*).\n\n Doom - Increases damage from 20/35/50 to (40/60/80*) and duration from 15 to (16*). Duration doesn\'t count down while the target is within 900 range of  Doom.\n\n Earth Spirit - Adds the  Enchant Remnant ability.\n\n Earthshaker - Causes each initial hero hit to echo twice.\n\n Elder Titan - Increases slow duration from 3 / 4 / 5 to (4 / 5 / 6*) and adds (4 / 5 / 6*) disarm.\n\n Enchantress - Increases attack range and cast range of  Impetus from 550 to (740*).\n\n Enigma - Adds  Midnight Pulse damage to your  Black Hole.\n\n Faceless Void - Increases duration from 4/4.5/5 to (4/5/6*) and decreases cooldown from 130/115/100 to (60*).\n\n Gyrocopter - Increases the damage of the second missile from 100/150/200 to (175/225/275*), and gives global cast range.\n\n Huskar - Increases damage dealt from 35% to (65%*) of target\'s current HP, reduces cooldown from 12 to (4*).\n\n Invoker - Decreases cooldown from 22/17/12/5 (16/8/4/2*) and removes mana cost from 20/40/60/80 to (0*).\n\n Jakiro - Increases cast range from 900 to (1800*), distance from 900 to (1800*), duration from 7 to (14*), and damage from 100/140/180 to (125/175/225*).\n\n Juggernaut - Increases number of jumps from 3/6/9 to (6/9/12*) and decreases cooldown from 130/120/110 to (70*).\n\n Keeper of the Light - Provides permanent Spirit Form. Additionally, the following effects are active during the day:  Keeper of the Light gains unobstructed vision and  Illuminate heals allies for 75% of the damage values.\n\n Legion Commander - Duel lasts until either Legion Commander or the Duel target die. Ends if duelists are ever more than 2,000 range apart.\n\n Leshrac - Increases damage from 100 / 130 / 160 to (160 / 190 / 220*)\n\n Lich - Increases damage from 280 / 370 / 460 to (370 / 460 / 550*) and casting range from 750 to (850*). Removes bounce limit from 10 to (Infinite*).\n\n Lifestealer - Grants Lifestealer  Assimilate ability.\n\n Lina - Increases  Laguna Blade\'s range from 600 to (900*), changes its damage type from Magical to Pure and allows it to slice through spell immunity.\n\n Lion - Increases damage from 600 / 725 / 850 to (725 / 875 / 1025*) and decreases cooldown for all levels from 160 / 100 / 40 to (100 / 60 / 20*), while decreasing mana cost for level 3 from 650 to (625*). Also causes  Finger of Death to hit units within a 200 AoE of the primary target.\n\n Lone Druid - Allows the Spirit Bear to attack at any range from Lone Druid and prevents it from dying when Lone Druid dies.\n\n Luna - Increases beams from 5/8/11 to (6/10/14), duration from 2.4/4.2/6 to (3/5.4/7.8), and max hits per unit from 5 to (6/10/14). Allows Eclipse to be cast on an area within 2500 range. Grants obstructed vision of that area. Can also target any allied unit to center Eclipse on their location, even while moving.\n\n Meepo - Adds an extra  Meepo. Number of  Meepos from 1 / 2 / 3 to (2 / 3 / 4*). Grants 100% shared attribute percentage.\n\n Morphling - Grants Morphling the Hybrid ability.\n\n Naga Siren - Regenerates Naga Siren and nearby allies by 6% of maximum health per second for the duration.\n\n Nature\'s Prophet - Increases damage from 140/180/225 to (155/210/275*), bounces from 16 to (18*) and units killed by Wrath of Nature spawn Nature\'s Call treants.\n\n Necrophos - Increases damage per HP missing from 0.4 / 0.6 / 0.9 to (0.6 / 0.9 / 1.2*), decreases mana cost for Level 1 from 175 to (150*), and decreases cooldown for levels 1 and 2 from 100 / 85 to (70*). Disables buyback for killed heroes.\n\n Night Stalker - Grants unobstructed vision in the night. The improved vision does not depend on using Darkness.\n\n Nyx Assassin - Grants Nyx Assassin the  Burrow ability.\n\n Ogre Magi - Adds the  Unrefined Fireblast ability.\n\n Omniknight - Affects buildings and gives global effect. Increases duration from 6 / 7 / 8 to (8 / 9 / 10*).\n\n Outworld Devourer - Increases damage multiplier from 8 / 9 / 10 to (9 / 10 / 11*) and casting range from 600 / 650 / 700 to (700 / 750 / 800*) and causes the ability to always trigger the mana loss on all heroes it damages..\n\n Phoenix - Allows  Phoenix to cast  Supernova on an allied hero, bringing both into the Sun to be reborn together.\n\n Puck - Increases damage from coil breaks from 100 / 150 / 200 to (200 / 250 / 300*), increases coil duration from 6 to (8*) and increases stun duration from 1.5 / 2.25 / 3 to (1.5 / 3 / 4.5*). Makes Coil-break stun pierce spell immunity.\n\n Pudge - Adds a strength-based damage bonus from 75 / 125 / 175 to (100%*), and heals  Pudge equal to the damage dealt by  Dismember.\n\n Pugna - Increases drain per second from 150/185/220 to (180/240/300), and sets cooldown time to zero.\n\n Queen of Pain - Reduces cooldown from 135 to (40*) and increases damage from 290 / 390 / 490 to (325 / 450 / 575*).\n\n Razor - Causes faster strikes from 0.7 / 0.6 / 0.5 to (0.6 / 0.5 / 0.4*) that can damage structures as well. When striking buildings, it will only target towers, barracks, and the Ancient.\n\n Rubick - Reduces cooldown from 20 / 18 / 16 to (2*) and increases cast range from 1000 to (1400*). Stolen spell receives  Aghanim\'s Scepter upgrade.\n\n Sand King - Decreases cooldown from 140 / 120 / 100 to (120 / 100 / 80*) and increases number of pulses from 6 / 8 / 10 to (8 / 10 / 12*).\n\n Shadow Demon - Cooldown is removed, replaced with three charges that replenish every 40 seconds, and applies Break on targets.\n\n Shadow Shaman - Increases ward damage from 40-45/ 55-60 / 70-75 to (85-90 / 105-110 /\n125-130*).\n\n Silencer - Applies current level of Curse of the Silent to all units.\n\n Skywrath Mage - Reduces cooldown from 60 / 40 / 20 to (20 / 10 / 0*).\n\n Spirit Breaker - Causes the  Greater Bash to hit an area around the initial target, decreases cooldown from 80 / 70 / 60 to (20*), and increases cast range from 700 to (850*).\n\n Sven -  God\'s Strength grants bonus damage to allies in the radius of 900.\n\n Techies - Increases damage from 300 / 450 / 600 to (450 / 600 / 750*) and cast range for all levels from 500 to (700*).\n\n Tinker - Causes Laser to bounce to nearby enemy heroes within a 550 range and doubles number of rockets launched from 2 to 4.\n\n Tiny - Allows  Tiny to equip a tree, increasing his attack range from 128 to (235*) (still considered as melee), (75%*) bonus damage versus buildings, and granting a cleave attack in a (400*) radius. Improves  Tossed unit damage from 35% / 50% / 65% to (50% / 65% / 80%*).\n\n Treant Protector - Adds  Eyes in the Forest ability. Makes  Overgrowth also affect and damage units within 800 range of  Eyes in the Forest trees.\n\n Tusk - Grants Tusk the  Walrus Kick ability.\n\n Undying - Increases damage amplification (Min. Damage Amplification: 5% / 10% / 15% (15% / 20% / 25%*) and percent of HP healed. Max. Damage Amplification: 20% / 25% / 30% (30% / 35% / 40%*)) and percent of HP healed (Own Max Health as Heal per Non-Hero Death: 2% (3%*). Own Max Health as Heal per Hero Death: 6% (10%*)).\n\n Vengeful Spirit - Decreases cooldown from 45 to (10*), and allows swapping of non-hero units.\n\n Venomancer - Increases damage from 36 / 58 / 81 to (58 / 81 / 108*), duration from 12 / 14 / 15 to (14 / 15 / 16*), and decreases cooldown from 140 / 120 / 100 to (140 / 120 / 60*).\n\n Viper - Decreases mana cost from 125 / 175 / 250 to (125*), cooldown from 80 / 50 / 30 to (12*), and increases cast range from 500 to (900*).\n\n Visage - Summons 3 familiars.\n\n Warlock - Calls 2 golems with 75% stats and 50% gold bounty.\n\n Weaver - Reduces cooldown from 60/50/40 to 20 and allows Timelapse to target allied heroes. Cast Range 1000.\n\n Windranger - Reduces cooldown from 60 to (15*) and decreases damage reduction from 50% / 40% / 30% to (30% / 15% / 0%*).\n\n Witch Doctor - Increases ward damage from 60 / 90 / 120 to (90 / 120 / 150*). Death Ward attacks will bounce 4 times.\n\n Wraith King - Allies who are within 1200 radius of Wraith King when slain become Wraiths for 5 seconds, delaying their death.\n\n Zeus - Increases damage from 225 / 350 / 475 to (440 / 540 / 640*).'),(5,'Animal Courier','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Consumables\nConsumable','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/animal-courier.png','Animal Courier\nActive: Summon Animal Courier\n\nCharges: 1\n\nCreature that carries items to and from your base.\nAdditional Information\nLosing the donkey is punishable by death.\n\nNotes:\n\nMoves at 280 movement speed\nInterupts the user\'s channeling spells upon cast.\nThe  Animal Courier is not a valid target for most spells. A list of spells which affect the courier can be found below.\nWhen the  Animal Courier dies, every allied player of the killing unit gains 30 * 7 the player\'s level in gold.\nThe  Animal Courier is invulnerable when near its team Fountain.'),(6,'Arcane Boots','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Support\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nTotal Cost: 1300','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/arcane-boots.png','Arcane Boots\nBonus:\n+250 Mana\n+15% Movement Speed\n\nActive: Replenish Mana\n\nRestores mana in an area around the hero.\n\nRadius: 900\nMana Restored: 160\n\n 55\n\nMagi equipped with these boots are valued in battle.\nAdditional Information\nAdditional Information:\n\nFlat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack.\n\n Arcane Boots can be disassembled.\n\nUsing Replenish Mana every time it is off cooldown is equivalent to 2.45 mana per second, which regenerates the bonus mana in 102 seconds.\n\nNotes:\n\nInterrupts the user\'s channeling spells upon cast.\nAffects every allied unit, including illusions invulnerable units, excluding wards and buildings.\n Meepo clones can not cast Replenish Mana.'),(7,'Apex','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/apex.png','Apex\nBonus:\n+75 Primary Attribute'),(8,'Arcane Ring','Active Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/arcane-ring.png','Arcane Ring\nBonus:\n+10 Intelligence\n+3 Armor\n\nCan be activated to restore 75 mana to all allies in a 1200 AoE.\n\n\n\n\n 40'),(9,'Arcane Rune','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/arcane-rune.png','Arcane Rune\nReduces cooldowns by 30% and mana costs by 40%.\n\nCooldown Reduction: 30%\nMana Cost Reduction: 40%\nDuration: 50\nAdditional Information\nNotes:\n\nReduces the cooldown/replenish time of all spells and items.\nAffects cooldowns of active and passive abilities.\nVisually reduces the cooldown of  Tranquil Boots (Active), but does not affect it.\nDoes not affect  Cloak and Dagger and  Drunken Brawler\'s certain critical/evasion timers.\nThe cooldown reduction is not updated dynamically. Only abilities cast while having the buff get their cooldowns reduced.\nBesides the mana cost reduction on items, all reductions are reflected in the ability tooltips.\nOnly affects the activation cost of spells. Mana cost over time is not reduced.\nStacks multiplicatively with the cooldown reduction of  Octarine Core.\nThe buff is applied to invulnerable and hidden units.\nThe buff of multiple Arcane Runes does not stack, but refreshes the duration instead.'),(10,'Armlet of Mordiggian','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Weapons\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 650  Total Cost: 2420','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/armlet-of-mordiggian.png','Armlet of Mordiggian\nBonus:\n+4 HP regeneration\n+15 Damage\n+5 Armor\n+25 Attack speed\n\nActive: Unholy Strength\n\nGives +31 damage, +4 armor and +25 strength while active, but drains 54 HP per second. The +4 armor bonus is given once the armlet is fully activated. You cannot die from the health loss when the bonus strength is gone, or the health drain per second.\n\nAttack Damage Bonus: 31\nAttack Speed Bonus: 10\nStrength Bonus: 25\nHealth Cost per Second: 40\nAdditional Information\nWeapon of choice among brutes, the bearer sacrifices his life energy to gain immense strength and power.\n\n\n\n\n\n Illusions do not benefit from the raw attack damage and speed bonus and do not lose health per second. Illusions gain the strength over 0.6 seconds and copy the original\'s current health, resulting in them having 475 current health more than the hero if it wasn\'t at full health as the illusion was created.'),(11,'Assault Cuirass','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nPassive Effect, Aura Effect\nRecipe Cost: 1300  Total Cost: 5250','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/assault-cuirass.png','Assault Cuirass\nBonus:\n+10 Armor\n+5 All Stats\n+30 Attack Speed\n\nPassive: Assault Aura\n\nGrants attack speed and armor to nearby allied units, and decreases armor for nearby enemies.\n\nRadius: 900\nBonus Attack Speed: 25\nBonus Armor: 5\nArmor Reduction: 5\nAdditional Information\nForged in the depths of the nether reaches, this hellish mail provides an army with increased armor and attack speed.\n\nTogether with the aura,  Assault Cuirass grants a total of 15 armor and 55 attack speed to the owner.\n\nNotes:\n\nFully stacks with other attack speed increasing, armor increasing and armor decreasing effects.\nAssault Auras from multiple Assault Cuirasses do not stack.\nA unit can be affected by the positive aura and the negative aura at the same time.\nThe aura\'s buff and debuff linger for 0.5 seconds.\nThe status buff icon on enemies only shows up when the affected unit has vision over the source.\nEnemy buildings are effected by the negative armor aura.\nAffects invulnerable allies and enemies.\nAttack speed aura bonus also affects buildings.'),(12,'Ballista','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/ballista.png','Ballista\nAttacks knock the enemies 50 distance back.\n\nBonus:\n+250 Attack Range\n+40 Pure Damage'),(13,'Band of Elvenskin','Shops: Main Shop, Side Lane Shop Categories: Attributes\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 450','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/band-of-elvenskin.png','Band of Elvenskin\nBonus:\n+6 Agility\nAdditional Information\nA tensile fabric often used for its light weight and ease of movement.\n\nAdditional Information:\n\nOne  Band of Elvenskin grants a total of 0.84 armor and 6 attack speed. Agility heroes also gain 6 attack damage.'),(14,'Battle Fury','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Weapons\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 4425','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/battle-fury.png','Battle Fury\nBonus:\n+7.5 HP/sec Regeneration\n+3.75 Mana Regeneration\n+60 Damage\n\nPassive: Cleave - Deals 70% of attack damage as physical damage in a cone up to 650 around the target. (Melee Only)\n\nCleave Radius: 360\nCleave Distance: 650\nCleave Damage: 70%\n\nPassive: Quell - Gives bonus attack damage against non-hero units, based on whether the equipped hero is ranged or melee.\n\nAttack Damage Bonus (melee): +50%\nAttack Damage Bonus (ranged): +25%\nAdditional Information\nThe bearer of this mighty axe gains the ability to cut down swaths of enemies at once.\n\nActive: Chop Tree - Destroys a target tree.\n\nCast Range: 350\n\n 4'),(15,'Belt of Strength','Shops: Main Shop, Side Lane Shop Categories: Attributes\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 450','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/belt-of-strength.png','Belt of Strength\nBonus:\n+6 Strength\nAdditional Information\nA valued accessory for improving vitality.\n\nCost Analysis:\n\nSelf Gold Value\n\n+6 Strength = 300g+6 Damage = 300g\nTotal Gold Value = 300g (600g)\n\nStatistical Efficiency\n\n Belt of Strength is 66.6% gold efficient for non-strength heroes and 133.3% gold efficent for strength heroes.\n\n\nAdditional Information:\n\nOne Belt of Strength grants a total of 114 health and 0.18 health regeneration. Strength heroes also gain 6 attack damage.'),(16,'Black King Bar','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nActive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 1375  Total Cost: 3975','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/black-king-bar.png','Black King Bar\nBonus:\n+10 Strength\n+24 Damage\n\nActive: Avatar\nGrants Spell Immunity and 100% Magic Damage Resistance. Duration and cooldown decrease with each use. Some Ultimate abilities are able to disable through Black King Bar.\n\nDuration: 10/9/8/7/6/5\n\n 80/75/70/65/60/55\nAdditional Information\nA powerful staff imbued with the strength of giants.\n\n Black King Bar can be sold. Repurchasing won\'t reset its duration.\n\nOne  Black King Bar grants a total of 190 health, 0.3 health regeneration and 24 (34 for strength heroes) attack damage.\n\nNotes:\n\nInterrupts the owner\'s channeling spells upon cast.\nThe spell immunity dispels many buffs and debuffs upon getting applied.\nList of removed buffs and debuffs can be found here.\nFor more details, including a list of spells which are not blocked, see Spell Immunity.'),(17,'Blade Mail','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nTotal Cost: 2200','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/blade-mail.png','Blade Mail\nBonus:\n+10 Intelligence\n+28 Damage\n+6 Armor\n\nActive: Damage Return\n\nReturns any damage you take to the unit that dealt the damage. Lasts 4.5 seconds.\n\nDamage Returned: 100%\nDuration: 4.5\n\n\n\n\n 25\n\n\n\n\n\n 25\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\nA razor-sharp coat of mail, it is the choice of selfless martyrs in combat.\n\nNotes:\n\nInterrupts the owner\'s channeling spells upon cast.\nReturns incoming damage after all reductions. So when damage is fully blocked, it won\'t return any damage.\nDoes not return damage from other  Blade Mails,  Spiked Carapace,  Heartstopper Aura,  Dispersion,  Poison Sting,  Corrosive Skin,  Fatal Bonds.\nFully ignores HP removal and self afflicted damage.\nReturns damage back to the source. This means it won\'t return damage from any summons to the hero, but to the summons instead.\nDoes not work against wards, buildings and allied units.'),(18,'Blade of Alacrity','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Attributes\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 1000','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/blade-of-alacrity.png','Blade of Alacrity\nBonus:\n+10 Agility\nAdditional Information\nA long blade imbued with time magic.\n\nAdditional Information:\n\nOne Blade of Alacrity grants a total of 1.4 armor and 10 attack speed. Agility heroes also gain 10 attack damage.'),(19,'Blades of Attack','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armaments\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 430','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/blades-of-attack.png','Blades of Attack\nBonus:\n+9 Damage\nAdditional Information\nThe damage of these small, concealable blades should not be underestimated.\n\nCost Analysis:\n\nStatistical Efficiency\n\n Blades of Attack is the item from which the damage gold value is derived, and as such, it derives a value of 50 gold per point of damage.'),(20,'Blight Stone','Total Cost: 300','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/blight-stone.png','Blight Stone\nPassive: Reduces armor by 2 on attack.\n\nNot an Unique Attack Modifier.'),(21,'Blink Dagger','Shops: Main Shop, Side Lane Shop Categories: Arcane\nActive Effect\nTotal Cost: 2250','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/blink-dagger.png','Blink Dagger\nActive: Blink\n\nTeleport to a target point up to 1200 units away. If damage is taken from an enemy hero, Blink Dagger cannot be used for 3 seconds.\n\nCast Range: Global\nMax Blink Distance: 1200\n\n\n\n\n\n\n 15\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\nThe fabled dagger used by the fastest assassin ever to walk the lands.\n\nNotes:\n\nDouble clicking the item automatically casts it on your team\'s fountain, blinking towards its direction.\nDoes not blink for the full distance when targeting closer than its max distance.\nWhen targeting beyond the max blink distance, it blinks for 960 range towards the targeted direction, instead of 1200.\nDisjoints projectile upon cast.\nCannot be cast while rooted.\nDamage greater than 0 (after reductions) coming from any player (including allies and self) and Roshan puts the dagger on a 3 second cooldown.\nSince it is a 3 second cooldown and not actually disabled, it can be refreshed with  Refresher Orb and  Rearm.'),(22,'Bloodstone','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 4900','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/bloodstone.png','Bloodstone\nBonus:\n+425 HP\n+425 Mana\n+16 Intelligence\n+12% Manacost and Manaloss Reduction\n+8% Base Spell Amplification\n\nActive: Transfer\nConverts 30% of your max mana to health over 2 seconds.\n\n\n\n\n 250\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nPassive: Mana Battery\nEach charge provides 0.2 mana regeneration and 0.35% spell amplification. Nearby kills provide 1 charge. Dying causes you to lose 3 charges. Starts with 14 charges. Provides 200% mana reg