s upon cast.\nDirectly increases the lifesteal granted by its passive part by 175%, resulting in 200% lifesteal.\nThe lifesteal stacks additively with other sources of lifesteal\nCannot lifesteal off of wards, buildings and allied units. Can lifesteal off of siege creeps.'),(187,'Scythe of Vyse','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Caster\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nTotal Cost: 5725','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/scythe-of-vyse.png','Scythe of Vyse\nBonus:\n+10 Strength\n+10 Agility\n+35 Intelligence\n+9 Mana Regeneration\n\nActive: Hex\n\nTurns a target unit into a harmless critter for 3.5 seconds. Destroys illusions.\n\nCast Range: 800\nDuration: 3.5\n\n\n\n\n 22\n\n\n\n\n\n 250\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\nThe most guarded relic among the cult of Vyse, it is the most coveted weapon among magi.'),(188,'Seer Stone','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/seer-stone.png','Seer Stone\nBonus:\n+350 Cast Range\n+350 Day and Night Vision\n+10 Mana Regen'),(189,'Sentry Ward','Shops: Main Categories: Consumables\nConsumable\nTotal Cost: 75','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/sentry-ward.png','Sentry Ward\nActive: Place Ward\n\nPlaces a Sentry Ward to give True Sight of the surrounding area. Lasts 8 minutes.\nHold Control to give one Sentry Ward to an allied hero.\n\nCast Range: 500\nTrue Sight Radius: 1000\nDuration: 240\n\n 1\nAdditional Information\nLike their counterparts,  Observer Wards,  Sentry Wards can be placed down anywhere to spot and assist. Unlike  Observer Wards, they have only temporary natural vision, but offer True Sight which can detect invisible enemies. Their detection radius is large, making them useful as long as you have vision in that area. Their primary use is for countering enemy wards, but can also be used for spotting invisible heroes by throwing one down where you expect them to show up.\n\n Sentry Wards have an initial stock of 3 sets in the store and a maximum stock of 5 sets, with each set containing 2 wards. The stock takes 90 seconds to replenish.\n\nNotes:\n\nProvides 150 radius ground vision at its location for 12 seconds.\nCan not be placed on the elevated area, including the ramp at the fountains or in Roshan\'s pit.\n Sentry Wards are fully shareable. However, holding Control allows the owner to give an ally just one ward, instead of the whole stack.\nIt is not possible to give couriers or  Lone Druid\'s  Summon Spirit Bear a  Sentry Ward by holding Control.\nThe True Sight is provided in its whole area, it is not obstructed by anything.\nThe True Sight is provided by an aura, its effect lingers for 0.5 seconds.\nCan not detect units under the effect of  Shadow Dance and  Smoke of Deceit.'),(190,'Shadow Amulet','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Arcane\nActive Effect\nTotal Cost: 1400','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/shadow-amulet.png','Shadow Amulet\nBonus:\n+30 Attack speed\n\nActive: Fade\n\nGrants invisibility to you or target allied hero over 1.25 seconds. Moving breaks the invisibility. There is no cooldown when using this item on yourself.\n\nCast Range: 600\nFade Time: 1.25\n\n 7(0 if used on self)\nAdditional Information\nNotes:\n\nDoes not interupt the user\'s channeling spells upon cast, neither when casting on self, nor when casting on allies.\nWhen casting on allies, the user does not have to face the targeted ally to cast it. Does not interrupt the target\'s channeling spells.\nDuring the fade time, the unit can still cast spells, use items and perform attacks.\nAfter the fade time, the unit automatically stops moving or attacking, but it does not stop spell casts.\nWhile invisible, the unit can turn and pick up or drop items without breaking the invisibility.\nWhile invisible, the unit is phased, means other units can walk through it without getting blocked.\nThe invisibility is broken upon reaching the cast point of spells or items or upon performing an attack.\nThe repositioning effects of the following spells also break the invisibility:\n Black Hole,  Vacuum,  Gust,  Deafening Blast,  Tornado,  Power Cogs,  Meat Hook, Adaptive Strike,  Telekinesis,  Primal Roar,  Skewer,  Flamebreak,  Boulder Smash,  Geomagnetic Grip,  Greater Bash,  Blinding Light,  Electric Vortex,  Toss,  Cyclone,  Snowball,  Eul\'s Scepter of Divinity and  Force Staff.'),(191,'Shadow Blade','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Weapons\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 1400  Total Cost: 2800','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/shadow-blade.png','Shadow Blade\nBonus:\n+27 Damage\n+30 Attack Speed\n\nActive: Shadow Walk\n\nMakes you invisible until the duration ends, or until you attack or cast a spell. While Shadow Walk is active, you move 20% faster and can move through units. If attacking to break the invisibility, you gain 175 bonus damage on that attack. Lasts 14 seconds.\n\nFade Time: 0.3\nDamage: 175\nDuration: 14\n\n\n\n\n 28\n\n\n\n\n\n 75\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\nThe blade of a fallen king, it allows you to move unseen and strike from the shadows.\n\nNotes:\n\nDoes not interrupt the owner\'s channeling spells upon cast.\nThe bonus damage is directly added to the attack damage, so it can be reduced with e.g.  Enfeeble or  Static Link.\nHowever, it cannot be amplified with e.g.  Empower or the  Rune of Double Damage.\nThe damage is considered by lifesteal, cleaves, Splash ( Elder Dragon Form) and  Psi Blades, but not by crits.\nDuring the fade time, the user can cast spells, use items and perform attacks without breaking the invisibility.\nThose attacks will apply the 175 damage to the target.\nThe bonus damage does not apply when attacking wards and buildings out of the invisibility.\nThe invisibility is lost upon reaching the cast point of spells, or upon finishing an attack, for ranged heroes this is upon projectile launch.\nThis means when the attack misses, the invisibility is still lost.\nAllows the user to path through other units, including wards, but not through buildings.\nThe user can pick up and drop items without breaking the invisibility.'),(192,'Shiva\'s Guard','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nActive Effect, Passive Effect, Aura Effect\nRecipe Cost: 650  Total Cost: 4750','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/shivas-guard.png','Shiva\'s Guard\nBonus:\n+30 Intelligence\n+15 Armor\n\nActive: Arctic Blast\n\nEmits a freezing wave that does 200 damage to enemies and slows their movement by 40% for 4 seconds.\n\nRadius: 900\nDamage: 200\nMove Speed Slow: 40%\nSlow Duration: 4\n\n\n\n\n 30\n\n\n\n\n\n 100\n\n\n\n\n\nPassive: Freezing Aura\n\nReduces attack speed on enemies.\n\nRadius: 900\nAttack Speed Slow: 45\nAdditional Information\nSaid to have belonged to a goddess, today it retains much of its former power.\n\nOne  Shiva\'s Guard grants a total of 15 armor, 390 mana and 1.2 mana regeneration (and 30 attack damage for intelligence heroes).\n\nNotes:\n\nDoes not interrupt the owner\'s channeling spells upon cast.\nThe blast spreads at a speed of 350.\nThe area of effect is centered around the owner, so when moving, the radius moves along.\nThe blast is not a ring. It affects every unit between the blast\'s edge and the caster.\nThis means it is not possible to avoid the blast by blinking towards the caster.\nProvides 800 radius flying vision, following the caster and leaving a trail of vision which lasts for 2 seconds.\nFreezing Auras from multiple Shiva\'s Gaurds don\'t stack.\nThe aura\'s debuff lingers for 0.5 seconds.\nThe status buff icon only shows up when the affected unit has vision over the source.'),(193,'Silver Edge','Recipe Cost: 600  Total Cost: 5550','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/silver-edge.png','Silver Edge\nBonus:\n+15 All Stats\n+45 Damage\n+30 Attack speed\n\nActive: Shadow Walk\n\nMakes you invisible for 14 seconds, or until you attack or cast a spell. While invisible, you move 25% faster and can move through units.\n\nAttacking to end the invisibility will deal 175 bonus physical damage to the target, and for 4 seconds, disable their passive abilities.\n\nFade Time: 0.3\nDamage: 175\nMove Speed Bonus: 25%\nInvisibility Duration: 14\nBreak Duration: 4\n\n\n\n\n\n 22\n\n\n\n\n\n 75\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\nOnce used to slay an unjust king, only to have the kingdom erupt into civil war in the aftermath.\n\n\n\n\n\n Applies damage on spell immune enemies. Does not apply debuff on spell immune enemies.'),(194,'Skull Basher','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Weapons\nPassive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 900  Total Cost: 2750','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/skull-basher.png','Skull Basher\nBonus:\n+10 Strength\n+25 Damage\n\n\n\nPassive: Bash\n\nGives a chance to stun for 1.5 seconds.\n\nProc Chance (Melee): 25%\nProc Chance (Ranged): 10%\nStun Duration: 1.4\nDamage: 100\n\n 2.3\nAdditional Information\nA feared weapon in the right hands, this maul\'s ability to shatter the defenses of its opponents should not be underestimated.\n\nNotes:\n\nBashes don\'t pierce evasion.\n Skull Basher\'s bash does not stack with the bash of  Abyssal Blade and other Skull Bashers.\nWhen obtaining multiple items with the bash ability, only the first bought one\'s bash works while the others are disabled.'),(195,'Slippers of Agility','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Attributes\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 145','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/slippers-of-agility.png','Slippers of Agility\nBonus:\n+3 Agility\nAdditional Information\nLight boots made from spider skin that tingles your senses.\n\nAdditional Information:\n\nOne  Slippers of Agility grants a total of 0.42 armor and 3 attack speed. Agility heroes also gain 3 attack damage.'),(196,'Smoke of Deceit','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Consumables\nConsumable\nTotal Cost: 80','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/smoke-of-deceit.png','Smoke of Deceit\nActive: Smoke of Deceit\n\nCharges: 1\n\nUpon activation, the user and all nearby allied player-controlled units gain invisibility and bonus movement speed for a brief time. Minimap icons will also be hidden. Upon moving within 1025 range of an enemy hero or tower, the invisibility and movement speed bonus is lost.\n\nEffect Radius: 1200\nDispel Radius: 1025\nFade Time: 0\nMove Speed Bonus: 15%\nDuration: 35\n\n 1\nAdditional Information\nThough it can\'t be used for daring escapes or to gain the upper hand in the middle of combat,  Smoke of Deceit plays a cunning role against a well-warded team. The added mobility makes it easy to set up surprise attacks or to slip behind enemies without being spotted. However, if a hero hidden with  Smoke of Deceit comes too close to an enemy hero or building, the effect ends, meaning you should keep your distance.  Smoke of Deceit is especially useful to get to Roshan undetected as many players ward the surrounding area.\n\n Smoke of Deceit is limited to a stock of 2 in the store. The stock takes 7 minutes to replenish.\n\nStacks with itself in inventory.\n\nCan be used by a Courier.\n\nNotes:\n\nInterrupts the user\'s channeling spells upon using.\nAffected unit can cast spells and use items while invisible without breaking it. However, attacking does break it.\nWhen attacking, the invisibility is lost upon reaching the attack point, even when the attack misses.\nInvisible units can pick up and drop items without breaking the invisibility.\nTrue Sight can not detect units affected by  Smoke of Deceit. The only exception is  Chronosphere.\nOnly affects player controlled units. Does not affect invulnerable allies, however, invulnerable enemy heroes or towers dispel it.\nThe effect is only dispelled when approaching an enemy hero (excluding illusions)or a tower.'),(197,'Solar Crest','Active Effect\nRecipe Cost: 300  Total Cost: 3875','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/solar-crest.png','Solar Crest\nBonus:\n+10 All Stats\n+12 Armor\n+20 Movement Speed\n+1.5 Mana Regen\n\nActive: Shine - Can be cast on allies or enemies, removing your own +12 Armor bonus. Grants allies +80 Attack Speed, +10% Movement Speed, +12 Armor. On enemies it applies -80 Attack Speed, -10% Movement Speed, -12 Armor\n\n\n 7\nAdditional Information\nA talisman forged to honor the daytime sky.'),(198,'Soul Booster','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 3300','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/soul-booster.png','Soul Booster\nBonus:\n+450 HP\n+400 Mana\nAdditional Information\nRegain lost courage.'),(199,'Soul Ring','Shops: Main Categories: Common\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 250  Total Cost: 765','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/soul-ring.png','Soul Ring\nBonus:\n+6 Strength\n+2.25 HP Regen\n\nActive: Sacrifice\n\nConsume 170 HP to temporarily gain 150 mana. Lasts 10 seconds.\n\nIf the mana gained cannot fit in your mana pool, it creates a buffer of mana that will be used before your mana pool.\n\nDuration: 10\n\n 25\nAdditional Information\nA ring that feeds on the souls of those around it.'),(200,'Spell Prism','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/spell-prism.png','Spell Prism\nBonus:\n+12 All Stats\n20% Cooldown Reduction\n+4 Mana Regeneration'),(201,'Spider Legs','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/spider-legs.png','Spider Legs\nBonus:\n+28% Movement Speed\n+50% Turn Rate\n\nCan be activated to gain free pathing and +28% movement speed for 3 seconds, destroys trees along the way.\n\n\n\n\n\n 10'),(202,'Spirit Vessel','Shops: Main Shop\nActive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 750  Total Cost: 2975','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/spirit-vessel.png','Spirit Vessel\nBonus:\n+2 Strength\n+2 Agility\n+2 Intelligence\n+250 Health\n+1 Mana Regen\n+2 Armor\n+20 Movement Speed\n\nActive: Soul Release\n\nWhen used against enemies, it deals 4% of current health per second as magic damage, and reduces HP regeneration and healing by 60%. Deals 25 damage per second.\n\nLasts 8 seconds.\n\nGains charges every time an enemy hero dies within 1400 units. Only the closest Spirit Vessel to the dying hero will gain a charge.'),(203,'Staff of Wizardry','Shops: Main 