ness and charges. The regeneration from Eating a Tree is also not broken when damage is taken, making this excellent for retreats. It can also be shared with allies, one charge at a time.\n\nStacks with itself in inventory.\n\nAs a target tree is removed on cast, it is useful for providing alternate pathways to escape from or chase an enemy.\n\nNotes:\n\nSuccessive uses with the same unit do not stack, but refresh the duration instead.\nRestores health in form of health regeneration, so it heals for 0.071875 health in 0.01 second intervals, which is 7.1875 health per second.\nThe targeted tree is instantly destroyed upon cast.\nCreates a  Tango (Shared) in the targeted ally\'s inventory.\nIf the targeted ally\'s inventory is full, the item is dropped on the ground.\nCan not be cast on  Lone Druid\'s  Summon Spirit Bear, but it is possible to directly put a  Tango (Shared) in its inventory.'),(207,'Tango (Shared)','Consumable, Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/tango-shared.png','Tango (Shared)\nActive: Eat Tree\n\nCharges: 1\n\nConsume a tree to restore health over time. Comes with 4 charges.\n\nCast Range: 165\nHealth restored: 115\nDuration: 32\n\n 60\nAdditional Information\n Tango (Shared) work exactly the same as regular  Tangos. If the receiving player has no room in his/her inventory, the Shared Tango will be created on the ground next to the hero. Shared  Tangos cannot be shared again, but can be dropped on the ground and used by any ally player who picks it up, including the original sharer.\n\nUnlike regular  Tangos however,  Tango (Shared) do not stack in the inventory.  Tango (Shared) also have a 60 second cooldown.\n\nNotes:\n\n[&] Using Tango on Iron Branch trees provides double healing duration.\nSuccessive uses with the same unit do not stack, but refresh the duration instead.\nRestores health in form of health regeneration, so it heals for 0.071875 health in 0.01 second intervals, which is 7.1875 health per second.\nThe targeted tree is instantly destroyed upon cast.'),(208,'Telescope','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/telescope.png','Telescope\nLowers Scan cooldown by 50%. Increases attack and cast range of nearby allies by 125.'),(209,'The Leveller','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/the-leveller.png','The Leveller\nBonus:\n+60 Attack Speed\n25% Demolish'),(210,'Third Eye','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/third-eye.png','Third Eye\nBonus:\n+7 All Stats\n\nGrants truesight in a 500 radius and +300 day and night vision. Has 3 charges that diminish with each death.'),(211,'Timeless Relic','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/timeless-relic.png','Timeless Relic\nBonus:\n+25% Debuff Duration Amplification\n+15% Spell Amplification'),(212,'Titan Sliver','','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/titan-sliver.png','Titan Sliver\nBonus:\n+16% Base Damage\n+16% Magic Resistance\n+16% Status Resistance'),(213,'Tome of Aghanim','Consumable','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/tome-of-aghanim.png','Tome of Aghanim\nCan be consumed to temporarily receive the  Aghanim\'s Scepter buff for 3 minutes.'),(214,'Tome of Knowledge','Total Cost: 150','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/tome-of-knowledge.png','Tome of Knowledge\nGrants you 700 experience plus 135 per tome consumed by your team.\nBase Experience Gained: 700\nBonus Experience Gained per Previous Tome: 135\n 300\nAdditional Information\nThe initial 10 minute stock of this item provides 2 tomes at once in the shop. Following replenishments provide single tomes.'),(215,'Town Portal Scroll','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Consumables\nConsumable\nTotal Cost: 90','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/town-portal-scroll.png','Town Portal Scroll\nActive: Teleport\n\nCharges: 1\n\nTeleports you to a target friendly building.\n\nCast Range: Global\nDistance to Building: 70 - 575\nChannel Time: 3 / 5 / 5.5 / 6 / 6.5 (1st / 2nd / 3rd / 4th / 5th teleport)\nRecent Teleport check radius: 1100\nRecent Teleport check duration: 25\n\n\n\n\n 80\n\n\n\n\n\n 75\n\n\n\n\n\nAdditional Information\nReading the scroll allows the casting hero to teleport to a friendly building. The  Town Portal Scroll is often used as a means of escape against heroes who have no way to cancel the channeling.'),(216,'Tranquil Boots','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Support\nActive Effect, Passive Effect\nTotal Cost: 975','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/tranquil-boots.png','Tranquil Boots\nBonus:\n+14 HP Regeneration\n+26% Movement Speed\n\nPassive: Break\n\nWhenever you attack or are attacked by a hero, the bonus 14 HP regen is lost and the movement speed bonus is reduced to 18% for 13 seconds.\nAdditional Information\n\n\n\n\n Illusions always have the broken version in their inventory.\n\nWhile they increase the longevity of the wearer, these boots are not particularly reliable.\n\nCannot be disassembled. Flat movement speed bonuses from multiple pairs of boots do not stack. The HP regeneration stacks with multiple  Tranquil Boots.\n\nNotes:\n\nNot disabled by creeps.\nBreaks upon successfully landing an attack on an enemy, or when an enemy successfully lands an attack on you.\nThis means when your or an enemy\'s attack evasion misses or is disjointed, the boots will not break.\nThe actual damage from the attack does not matter.\nWhen triggered, the item\'s icon changes and is set on a 13 second cooldown. However, this has only informative purposes.\nThis means that refreshing it ( Refresher Orb,  Rearm) does not skip the broken state.'),(217,'Trident','','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/trident.png','Trident\nCan be combined with  Sange,  Yasha and  Kaya together. Grants +30 Agility, +30 Strength, +30 Intelligence, +30 Movement Speed, +30 Attack Speed, +30 Status Resistance, +30% Mana Loss Reduction, +30% Regen and Lifesteal Amplification and +30% Spell Amplification.'),(218,'Trusty Shovel','','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/trusty-shovel.png','Trusty Shovel\nBonus:\n+100 Health\n\nCan be activated to dig with a 1 second channel. Can find a  Bounty Rune, a Flask, a 2 charged  Town Portal Scroll bundle, or an enemy Kobold.\n\nThe same reward cannot appear back to back.\n\n\n\n\n 55'),(219,'Ultimate Orb','Shops: Secret Shop Categories: Attributes\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 2150','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/ultimate-orb.png','Ultimate Orb\nBonus:\n+10 Strength\n+10 Agility\n+10 Intelligence\nAdditional Information\nA mystical orb containing the essence of life.\n\nAdditional Information:\n\nOne  Ultimate Orb grants a total of 190 health, 0.3 health regeneration, 1.4 armor, 10 attack speed, 130 mana, 0.4 mana regeneration and 10 attack damage.'),(220,'Urn of Shadows','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Support\nPassive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 310  Total Cost: 865','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/urn-of-shadows.png','Urn of Shadows\nBonus:\n+2 All Stats\n+2 Armor\n+1.5 Mana Regen\n\nActive: Soul Release\n\nHeals HP over time for friendly units, but deals magical damage over time for enemy units. The healing effect is lost if the affected unit takes damage from an enemy hero or tower.\n\nCast Range: 950\nAllied Heal per Second: 30[/color\nAllied Total Heal: 240\nEnemy Damage per Second: 18.75\nEnemy Total Damage: 200\nHeal/Damage Duration: 8\n\n 7\nAdditional Information\n\n\n\n\n Can be cast on spell immune allies, but not enemies.\n\nContains the ashes of powerful demons.\n\nGains 1 charge every time an enemy hero dies within a 1400 radius. Only the closest Urn to the dying hero will gain a charge. Empty urns gain 2 charges, instead of 1.\n\nNotes:\n\nDouble clicking the item uses it on self.\nSuccessive casts on the same allied target do not stack, but refresh the duration instead.\nHowever, successive casts on enemy targets fully stack and work independent from each other.\nHeals 12.5 health in 0.25 second intervals, resulting in 32 heal instances.\nDeals 18.75 damage in 1 second intervals, resulting in 8 damage instances.\nThe heal is dispelled by any damage coming from players (before reductions), including self afflicted damage, and from towers.\nRoshan and the Fountain attacks do not dispel the heal.\nIs not dispelled by health cost of spells, health manipulating spells, negative regeneration,  Poison Sting and  Dispersion.\nCan be cast on illusions,  Lone Druid\'s  Summon Spirit Bear,  Visage\'s  Summon Familiars,  Warlock\'s Golem and the  Primal Split spirits.'),(221,'Vambrace','','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/vambrace.png','Vambrace\nBonus:\n+10 Selected Attribute\n+5 Other Attributes\n+8% Magic Resistance or +10 Attack Speed or +5% Spell Damage\n\nActive: Switch Attribute\n\nChanges selected attribute between Strength, Agility and Intelligence.'),(222,'Vampire Fangs','Passive Effect','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/vampire-fangs.png','Vampire Fangs\nBonus:\n+6% Lifesteal\n+15% Spell Lifesteal\n+250 Night Vision'),(223,'Vanguard','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Armor\nPassive Effect\nTotal Cost: 1925','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/vanguard.png','Vanguard\nBonus:\n+250 HP\n+7 HP Regeneration\n\nPassive: Damage Block\n\nGives the wielder a chance to block damage from each incoming attack based on whether the equipped hero is melee or ranged.\n\nProc Chance: 50%\nBlocked Damage (melee): 70\nBlocked Damage (ranged): 35\nAdditional Information\nA powerful shield that defends its wielder from even the most vicious of attacks.\n\nNotes:\n\nDoes not work against wards ( Plague Ward,  Mass Serpent Ward,  Death Ward).'),(224,'Veil of Discord','Shops: Main Shop Categories: Caster\nActive Effect\nRecipe Cost: 1150  Total Cost: 2050','https://www.dotafire.com/images/item/veil-of-discord.png','Veil of Discord\nBonus:\n+6 Strength\n+6 Agility\n+15 Intelligence\n+5 Health Regeneration\n+6 Armor\n\nActive: Magic Weakness\n\nEmits a weakening blast that increases the magic damage enemies take. Lasts 16 seconds.\n\nCast Range: 1000\nRadius: 600\nSpell Damage 